The paper deals with the problem of identifying and localizing link faults in complex networks, which is a key issue in the field of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed solution involves using machine learning techniques to analyze traffic behavior, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the potential security implications of link faults, which could place it under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of machine learning to optimize network performance could also place it under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
